\v 17 Ephraim\f + \fr 4:17 \ft Ephraim was the leading tribe of the northern kingdom of Israel and so was often used to describe the whole kingdom.\f* \w is|strong="H2266"\w* bewitched\f + \fr 4:17 \ft The word used can mean “joined to” or “enchanted, under a spell.”\f* by \w idols|strong="H6091"\w*, so \w leave|strong="H3240"\w* \w him|strong="H3240"\w* \w alone|strong="H3240"\w*!  
