\v 2 Judgment belongs \w with|strong="H3605"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w*\f + \fr 5:2 \ft The phrase is literally “for you the judgment” and so is ambiguous. It could simply mean that God's judgment is against these leaders; but it could also mean that the power of judgment belongs to them and they have not exercised this authority wisely.\f* \w because|strong="H3605"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w* \w have|strong="H3605"\w* \w been|strong="H3605"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* snare set \w at|strong="H3605"\w* Mizpah \w and|strong="H3605"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* net spread \w out|strong="H3605"\w* \w on|strong="H3605"\w* Tabor.\f + \fr 5:2 \ft Both Mizpah and Mt. Tabor had particular historical significance for Israel but are now sites of degradation.\f* \w You|strong="H3605"\w* dug \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w deep|strong="H6009"\w* trap \w in|strong="H3605"\w* Shittim,\f + \fr 5:2 \ft Shittim was the last place the Israelites camped before crossing the Jordan (\xt Numbers 25\ft ).\f* \w but|strong="H3605"\w* \w I|strong="H3605"\w* \w will|strong="H3605"\w* punish \w you|strong="H3605"\w* \w for|strong="H3605"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w these|strong="H3605"\w* \w things|strong="H3605"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w* \w have|strong="H3605"\w* \w done|strong="H3605"\w*.  
