\v 11 \w The|strong="H3588"\w* people \w of|strong="H4941"\w* Ephraim \w are|strong="H4941"\w* \w crushed|strong="H7533"\w*, smashed \w to|strong="H1980"\w* pieces \w in|strong="H1980"\w* \w judgment|strong="H4941"\w* \w because|strong="H3588"\w* \w they|strong="H3588"\w* \w were|strong="H4941"\w* \w determined|strong="H2974"\w* \w to|strong="H1980"\w* \w follow|strong="H1980"\w* human commands.\f + \fr 5:11 \ft This verse has been linked to the decision of King Menahem of Israel's decision to agree to a huge payment in silver to the Assyrian king as a means of avoiding conflict (see \xt 2 Kings 15:19-20\ft ). Others have thought the “human commands” are Jeroboam's institution of calves as images to worship (\xt 1 Kings 12\ft ). Alternatively the end of this verse could also be translated “determined to follow idolatry.”\f*  
