\v 11 \w In|strong="H4428"\w* \w my|strong="H5414"\w* \w anger|strong="H5678"\w* \w I|strong="H5414"\w* \w give|strong="H5414"\w* \w you|strong="H5414"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w king|strong="H4428"\w*, \w and|strong="H4428"\w* \w in|strong="H4428"\w* \w my|strong="H5414"\w* \w fury|strong="H5678"\w* \w I|strong="H5414"\w* \w take|strong="H3947"\w* \w one|strong="H4428"\w*.\f + \fr 13:11 \ft The verb forms used here are not past tense, so the usual translation referring back to God's provision of King Saul in response to the people's demands is problematic here. Since Hosea is dealing with the present situation of the northern kingdom, one interpretation is that the king God is giving is the king of Assyria, and the one he is taking is the king of Israel. Though in the previous verse God does mention the people's previous demand for a king, he begins that verse with the current question, “Where then is your king?”\f*   
\p
\v 12 Ephraim's \w guilt|strong="H5771"\w* \w is|strong="H5771"\w* packed \w up|strong="H6845"\w*; \w their|strong="H6845"\w* \w sin|strong="H2403"\w* \w will|strong="H5771"\w* \w be|strong="H2403"\w* eradicated.\f + \fr 13:12 \ft “Eradicated”: literally, “concealed.” What Hosea seems to be saying is that Israel's sins have come to the point that God has to take action by eliminating the problem by allowing invasion and exile. The worship of Baal has to be ended (“concealed”—but not in sense of it being simply hidden away and continuing). \f*  
\v 13 \w The|strong="H3588"\w* \w pain|strong="H2256"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w childbirth|strong="H3205"\w* \w has|strong="H3588"\w* \w come|strong="H3205"\w* \w to|strong="H6256"\w* \w them|strong="H5975"\w*, trying \w to|strong="H6256"\w* \w give|strong="H3205"\w* \w birth|strong="H3205"\w* \w to|strong="H6256"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w who|strong="H1931"\w* \w is|strong="H1931"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* “\w wise|strong="H2450"\w*” \w because|strong="H3588"\w* \w he|strong="H1931"\w* \w is|strong="H1931"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w in|strong="H5975"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* right \w position|strong="H5975"\w* \w when|strong="H3588"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* \w time|strong="H6256"\w* comes.\f + \fr 13:13 \ft This could refer to the problems of a breech baby delivery in which both mother and baby could potentially die.\f*   
\p
